  "32 - After-sales hydraulic bleeling procedure for ABS S-lot": {
   "width": 14460,
   "height": 11460,
   "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
   "labels": [
    {
     "text": "This sequence is only used for ABS on S-lot vehicle (due to ABS SW bug)",
     "color": "rgb(0,128,255)",
     "alignment": "2",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 120,
      "top": 480,
      "height": 480,
      "width": 14400
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 16.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "-1- Place the bleeding tool on the brake liquid tank",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(15,15,15)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 240,
      "top": 1080,
      "height": 360,
      "width": 14160
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "-3- Make sure that all bleeding screws are closed",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(15,15,15)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 240,
      "top": 2040,
      "height": 360,
      "width": 14160
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "",
     "color": "rgb(128,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,255)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 10800,
      "top": 3240,
      "height": 6600,
      "width": 3600
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "1"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "-2- Perform a manual bleeding on the four wheels without any ABS or ESC activation (primary bleeding)",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(255,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 240,
      "top": 1560,
      "height": 360,
      "width": 14160
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "-5- Click on button preliminary flush cycle and wait the end of the control (duration = 20 sec.)",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(15,15,15)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 240,
      "top": 3240,
      "height": 720,
      "width": 10320
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "-11- When no air is remaining, close the FR bleeding screw and then stop the FR bleeding procedure",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(15,15,15)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 240,
      "top": 8280,
      "height": 720,
      "width": 10320
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "-12- When FR bleeding is over, click on the button flush cycle and wait the end of the control (duration = 20 sec.)",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(15,15,15)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 240,
      "top": 9120,
      "height": 720,
      "width": 10320
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "-10- If air bubbles were still present when the procedure stopped, reactivate the FR bleeding procedure until no air is present (return to step 10)",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(15,15,15)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 240,
      "top": 7440,
      "height": 720,
      "width": 10320
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "-6- When flush cycle is over, activate the FL bleeding procedure and then open the FL bleeding screw (duration = 30 sec.)",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(15,15,15)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 240,
      "top": 4080,
      "height": 720,
      "width": 10320
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "-7- If air bubbles were still present when the procedure stopped, reactivate the FL bleeding procedure until no air is present (return to step 7)",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(15,15,15)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 240,
      "top": 4920,
      "height": 720,
      "width": 10320
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "-9- When FL bleeding is over, activate the FR bleeding procedure and then open the FR bleeding screw (duration = 30 sec.)",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(15,15,15)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 240,
      "top": 6600,
      "height": 720,
      "width": 10320
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "-4- ALL ALONG the procedure (from step 5 to step 15), the brake pedal must be pressed and released alternately (approx. 3 sec. pressed / 3 sec. released)",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(255,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 240,
      "top": 2520,
      "height": 600,
      "width": 14160
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "-14- Perform a manual bleeding on the RR bleeding screw (primary bleeding on FL/RR axis)",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(255,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 240,
      "top": 10440,
      "height": 360,
      "width": 14160
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "-13- Perform a manual bleeding on the RL bleeding screw (primary bleeding on FR/RL axis)",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(255,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 240,
      "top": 9960,
      "height": 360,
      "width": 14160
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "",
     "color": "rgb(223,223,223)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 120,
      "top": 960,
      "height": 10440,
      "width": 14400
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "MS Sans Serif",
      "size": 8.25,
      "bold": "0",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "-15- You can release the brake pedal and stop and disconnect the bleeding tool ",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(255,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 240,
      "top": 10920,
      "height": 360,
      "width": 14160
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "ABS  / ESC Internal control status",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "2",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(0,0,0)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 11040,
      "top": 6000,
      "height": 600,
      "width": 3120
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "MS Sans Serif",
      "size": 10.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
     "text": "-8- When no air is remaining, close the FL bleeding screw and stop the FL bleeding procedure",
     "color": "rgb(255,255,255)",
     "alignment": "0",
     "fontcolor": "rgb(15,15,15)",
     "bbox": {
      "left": 240,
      "top": 5760,
      "height": 720,
      "width": 10320
     },
     "font": {
      "name": "Arial",
      "size": 12.0,
      "bold": "1",
      "italic": "0"
     }
    },
    {
